Or jurm kiya hai toh bhi bata, ye jurm ki jurm ki kya hai sazaa

Tumhe hum se badh kar duniya, duniya tumhe humse badhkar
Dil galti kar baitha hai,galti kar baitha hai dil
Haaye dil galti kar baitha tu bol kaffara kya hoga

Synopsis:
Yash Raj Films’ Saiyaara is an intense love story, that launches Ahaan Panday and Aneet Padda as the next YRF hero and heroine respectively. 

Directed by Mohit Suri, a master of the romance genre, Saiyaara tells a pure-hearted love story of two youngsters Vaani and Krish. While Vaani writes, Krish sings and they both make music together. Though poles apart in their lives, beliefs and backgrounds, Vaani and Krish are perfect with each other and for each other. Will they understand that truth despite their age, their problems? 

They say flawed, imperfect people make for a perfect love story…and Saiyaara is about celebrating that one love story that is so deep, so pure and so caring that it is absolutely unconditional.

Vaani and Krish will have to navigate life, their problems, their insecurities to hopefully realise that only love can be the answer to everything. Saiyaara is a film that celebrates every season of love through the eyes of Vaani & Krish and poses a simple question…do you love someone so much that you would bet everything to keep that person in your life?

snippet.title: HAQ | Official Teaser | Yami Gautam Dhar, Emraan Hashmi | Suparn S Varma | In Cinemas 7th Nov
snippet.description:
Shazia Bano takes her husband Abbas to court after he abandons her and their children, sparking a national battle over faith, women’s rights, and justice. Inspired by the landmark Supreme Court judgement of Mohd. Ahmed Khan vs. Shah Bano Begum. Haq is the story of one woman’s fight for her rights and justice. 

Releasing in cinemas on 7th November

HAQ is a fictionalized and dramatized version of events stated in the book titled ‘Bano: Bharat ki Beti’ written by Jigna Vora.

snippet.title: Mallo Bia | Naeem Dilpul | Gazzain Omer | Fariq Riaz | Official Music Video
snippet.description:
I feel a deep yearning inside my soul for someone and an intense longing that might never be understood. But, it makes me create melodies and melodies create music. Mallo Bia is the musical dot that connects me to my unseen whole. Hope, it gets due credit and appreciation as a piece of art. 

Title: Mallo Bia
Composition & Vocals: Naeem Dilpul
Poet: Gazzain Omer
Music: Ien Jouseph
Benjo: Dadullah Baloch
Director & DOP: Fariq Riaz
Edit: Fariq Riaz
Artists: Hafeez Lal, Homer Kiyya, Ehsan Danish, Zahid Zamur, Irfan Noor, Iqra Ali, Gam Baloch, S Baloch, Jalil Baloch, Faaz Baloch
Drone Shots: Hammal Salar & Tahir Hassan & Haseem Baloch
Makeup and styling: Sadiq 
Talent Coordinator: Sultan Sahil
AD: Sajjad Baloch
Pasni coordinator : Syed Saleem sher
Gwadar Coordinator: Meeran Baloch

Special Thanks
During the shooting of this song in Turbat, Dasht, Gwadar, Pasni and Karachi, many lovely people helped us greatly. Our team extends its special thanks to Kamal Khosa, Mujeeb Azad, Rashid Hasrat, Tahir Hassan, Ayaz Aslam, Daad Baloch, Usama, Behram Khan, Arman Akbar, Ilyas Baksh, Meer Dost, Tariq Syed, Zakria Hajiz, Didag Bashir, Kamran Ahmed, Qaiser Mukhtar, Sharbat Gul, Meeran Baloch, Zayn Murad, Shahid Rind, Khuda Baksh Halwai, Karimok Hotel, Irshad Baloch, Nawab Baloch, Charag Baloch, Iqbal Murad, Hammal Baloch Changaiz Baloch, Arif Baloch Gwadar, Syed Saleem Sher, Ziad Baloch, DK Baloch, Sadiq Saba, Jamal Baloch, Sane Albalushi, Zakir Dad and Shakir Shaad

Lyrics Translation

Come waltzing my way
In graceful trance

Let your hair, your locks, your curls softly lie,
Flowing down your thighs
Embrace me with passion
Till I dissolve completely, lost in your arms.

Your marble-sculpted form, serene and fair,
Like Eden’s garden, beyond compare.
You are my everything, my heart’s own art,
Your words enchant and captivate my heart.

O duchess fair of Shaal’s embrace,
To you I’m bound, your gentle grace.
My eyes shall follow where you shine,
I am yours, and you are mine.


Wait but a moment, linger, remain,
Gaze upon your Gazzain again.
Within his eyes, where shadows gleam,
Hang the echoes of an ancient dream.

snippet.title: Marvel Animation's Marvel Zombies - Official Teaser Trailer #2 (2025) Elizabeth Olsen, Paul Rudd
snippet.description:
Don't miss the Teaser Trailer #2 for Marvel Animation’s Marvel Zombies, an animated horror installment to the Marvel Cinematic Universe distributed by Marvel Studios. This series re-contextualizes the Marvel Universe as Earth's mightiest heroes go head-to-head against a zombie outbreak, turning even the strongest of them into undead nightmares. Marvel Animation’s Marvel Zombies will be a four-part event on September 24, streaming exclusively on Disney+.

After the Avengers are overtaken by a zombie plague, a desperate group of survivors discover the key to bringing an end to the super-powered undead, racing across a dystopian landscape and risking life and limb to save their world. 
 
Marvel Zombies stars Elizabeth Olsen, Paul Rudd, Florence Pugh, David Harbour, Tessa Thompson, Simu Liu, Awkwafina, Hailee Steinfeld, Wyatt Russell, Randall Park, Iman Vellani, Dominique Thorne, and more. The series is executive produced by Kevin Feige, Louis D’Esposito, Brad Winderbaum, Dana Vasquez-Eberhardt, Bryan Andrews, and Zeb Wells, and is produced by Danielle Costa, Carrie Wassenaar. 

Marvel Animation’s Marvel Zombies will be a four-part event on September 24, streaming exclusively on Disney+.

#IGN #Marvel #MCU

snippet.title: Two Much With Kajol And Twinkle - Official Trailer | Prime Video India
snippet.description:
Prime Video India Presents
Two Much With Kajol And Twinkle Official Trailer
Starring Kajol, Twinkle Khanna, Salman Khan, Aamir Khan, Govinda, Chunky Panday, Vicky Kaushal, Kriti Sanon, Varun Dhawan, Alia Bhatt, Janhvi Kapoor, Karan Johar.
Created by Banijay Asia

Official Release Date September 25, 2025 on Prime Video India.

About:
Kajol and Twinkle are serving up a talk show with a twist - equal parts masti, magic and maybe even some manic energy. Expect wild hot takes, controversial opinions and the kind of honesty that makes you say, “Dude, same!” 
Joining them are their friends who just happen to be some of the biggest stars in the country (and even the world). With eight unique pairs gracing the couch this season, the conversations jump from filmy nostalgia to family drama, love, paparazzi, fame and everything in between.
What sets it apart is the unapologetic female gaze - a perspective that’s funny, sharp, and not afraid to hold up a mirror to society. One moment you’re laughing embarrassingly loudly, the next you’re caught off guard by an insight that might make you question your own life choices. 
Basically, it’s a vibe: two women side-by-side, yapping with their friends. Think of it as the fun table at the party, sunny, chatty, and just unhinged enough to keep you hooked.


Follow us on:
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/primevideoin/
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/PrimeVideoIN/
X: https://x.com/PrimeVideoIN

Prime Video is a one-stop entertainment destination offering customers a vast collection of premium programming in one application available across several devices. On Prime Video, customers can find their favourite Indian and international original series, movies, TV shows, and more, across multiple languages – including Indian-produced Original series like Mirzapur, Farzi, Panchayat, The Family Man, Dhootha, Jubilee, Dahaad, Made in Heaven, Suzhal – The Vortex, Inspector Rishi, Poacher, Indian Police Force, Paatal Lok, Rainbow Rishta, Wedding.con; Original movies like Maja Ma, Ammu, Mast Mein Rehne Ka; popular global Originals like Citadel, The Lord of The Rings: The Rings of Power, Fallout, Reacher, The Boys, The Wheel of Time, Road House, The Idea of You; some of the biggest post-theatrical films; direct-to-service films such as Shershaah, Soorarai Pottru, Sardar Udham, Bawaal, Gehraiyaan, Jai Bhim, Jalsa, Sherni, Narappa, Sarpatta Parambarai, Kuruthi, Joji, Malik, Pippa, HOME, Sharmajee Ki Beti, and many more of such titles. Additionally, Prime Video’s video entertainment marketplace, offers customers programming from partners such as Lionsgate Play, Discovery+ Crunchyroll, BBC Player, Sony Pictures – Stream, MGM+, FanCode, Chaupal, Manorama Max, Eros Now, Hoichoi, Anime Times, to name a few, via Prime Video add-on-subscriptions, as well as the option to rent movies, regardless of whether customers have a Prime membership or not. Customers can also go behind the scenes of their favorite movies and series with exclusive X-Ray access.
